TR Location Analysis

Introduction

This document describes an analysis of the location of various TR types in proteins associated with signalling pathways commonly implicated in CRC. The five main pathways analysed were: WNT, P53, PI3K, TGF-beta and RAS-MAPK. Proteins belonging to each pathway were obtained by querying UniProt for reviewed human proteins associated with a certain pathway. The set of proteins for each pathway was supplemented using lists of curated genes that are often affected in cancer. These lists were taken from Sanchez-Vega (2018) https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6070353/. For each gene, the encoded proteins were queried from UniProt and merged with the previously obtained set of proteins for each pathway. This resulted in the following number of proteins per pathway: WNT (698), P53 (701), PI3K (311), TGF-Beta (264), RAS-MAPK (126). In addition, proteins belonging to the DNA mismatch-repair (MMR) system were analysed (26 proteins, TODO), as well as proteins associated with favourable (404) or unfavourable (286) CRC prognosis in the Human Protein Atlas https://www.proteinatlas.org/humanproteome/pathology/colorectal+cancer.
